cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the application of NOMA techniques in HUDNs to support massive connectivity in 5G systems, which is a networking and internet architecture problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a unified NOMA framework, including power-domain NOMA and code-domain NOMA, which involves information theory concepts. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper discusses user association and resource allocation in NOMA enabled HUDNs, which are communication and networking problems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper investigates the effectiveness of unified NOMA enabled HUDNs, which can be considered as a system control problem. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the use of NOMA techniques to enhance spectrum efficiency, which can be related to multimedia applications that require high bandwidth and low latency.
